00:00:05.130 --> 00:00:08.090
- Good afternoon and welcome.

00:00:08.090 --> 00:00:10.990
I'm Tomiko Brown-Nagin, the
dean of the Radcliffe Institute.

00:00:10.990 --> 00:00:15.350
And we are delighted to have
all of you here with us today.

00:00:15.350 --> 00:00:18.910
Let me start by thanking
VIDA, women in literary arts,

00:00:18.910 --> 00:00:20.440
for partnering with
the Schlesinger

00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:24.410
Library on the History of
Women to organize this event.

00:00:24.410 --> 00:00:26.890
And of course, I'm grateful
to this remarkable group

00:00:26.890 --> 00:00:30.010
of panelists and our
distinguished moderator

00:00:30.010 --> 00:00:32.259
for agreeing to participate
in what promises

00:00:32.259 --> 00:00:36.220
to be a fascinating discussion.

00:00:36.220 --> 00:00:39.970
Today's program is a part
of a yearlong celebration

00:00:39.970 --> 00:00:44.390
