the Schlesinger Library.

00:00:44.390 --> 00:00:47.950
And I understand that we're also
marking the 10th anniversary

00:00:47.950 --> 00:00:51.400
of the VIDA Count, an
annual inventory of gender

00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:55.690
disparity in major literary
publications and book reviews.

00:00:55.690 --> 00:00:59.620
Here at Radcliffe and
at VIDA, too, I imagine,

00:00:59.620 --> 00:01:03.790
anniversaries are about
more than commemoration.

00:01:03.790 --> 00:01:07.180
They're are also
about taking stock.

00:01:07.180 --> 00:01:10.070
They provide an opportunity
to reflect on progress,

00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:13.800
but also to chart
the work ahead,

00:01:13.800 --> 00:01:17.870
the work towards the objectives
that we've set for our society

00:01:17.870 --> 00:01:21.730
and for ourselves as advocates
of equality and opportunity

00:01:21.730 --> 00:01:23.560
for all.

00:01:23.560 --> 00:01:27.280
For that reason, I'm thrilled
that today's panel will focus

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:32.200
our attention on feminisms
now, where we find ourselves

00:01:32.200 --> 00:01:35.020
and where we aim to go.

00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:37.270
Over the next few
years, we at Radcliffe

00:01:37.270 --> 00:01:41.140
will engage in more of
this kind of taking stock

00:01:41.140 --> 00:01:45.100
as we critically examine the
centennial of women's suffrage

00:01:45.100 --> 00:01:46.720
in the United States.

00:01:46.720 --> 00:01:51.070
And on Monday, October 29, we
will continue our Schlesinger

00:01:51.070 --> 00:01:55.510
75th anniversary programming
with a performance

00:01:55.510 --> 00:01:59.740
from Shaina Taub's important
new musical, The Suffragist,

00:01:59.740 --> 00:02:02.740
followed by a panel discussion.

00:02:02.740 --> 00:02:06.340
I hope many of you will
register online and join us

00:02:06.340 --> 00:02:08.479
for that event.

00:02:08.479 --> 00:02:10.389
And now it's my
distinct pleasure

00:02:10.389 --> 00:02:12.760
to turn things over
to Jane Kamensky, who

00:02:12.760 --> 00:02:14.950
will introduce our panel.

00:02:14.950 --> 00:02:17.740
Jane is the Pforzheimer
Foundation director

00:02:17.740 --> 00:02:21.250
of the Schlesinger Library here
at Radcliffe and the Trumbull

00:02:21.250 --> 00:02:24.670
Professor of American History
in the faculty of Arts

00:02:24.670 --> 00:02:25.900
and Sciences.

00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:27.216
Jane.

