out with them.

00:54:29.850 --> 00:54:32.000
I never experience
more joy than when

00:54:32.000 --> 00:54:33.680
we are laughing and giggling.

00:54:33.680 --> 00:54:35.580
That is important.

00:54:35.580 --> 00:54:38.150
But I also want to underscore
our community and the people

00:54:38.150 --> 00:54:41.300
who are drawn to my
work that we have

00:54:41.300 --> 00:54:44.564
to interrogate how our joys
bring other people pain.

00:54:44.564 --> 00:54:45.980
And that doesn't
mean that we have

00:54:45.980 --> 00:54:47.900
to live in that place of shame.

00:54:47.900 --> 00:54:51.290
It doesn't mean that we have
to be self-flagellating.

00:54:51.290 --> 00:54:53.210
It just means that we
have to be conscientious

00:54:53.210 --> 00:54:55.530
as we move through the world.

00:54:55.530 --> 00:55:01.290
Another part of what I try to
do is to underscore the fact--

00:55:01.290 --> 00:55:04.310
in doing a lot of research,
I have talked and interviewed

00:55:04.310 --> 00:55:06.530
a lot of OG black feminists.

00:55:06.530 --> 00:55:08.440
I read all the time.

00:55:08.440 --> 00:55:11.280
That's a part of my robust
citational practice.

00:55:11.280 --> 00:55:15.830
And I try to underscore the
fact that sometimes, especially

00:55:15.830 --> 00:55:18.740
online when we're just
trading these thoughts

00:55:18.740 --> 00:55:21.860
and theorizing really,
really quickly, we

00:55:21.860 --> 00:55:26.780
have a tendency to think that
we are reinventing the wheel.

00:55:26.780 --> 00:55:33.020
So take for example,
sexual bodily autonomy.

00:55:33.020 --> 00:55:35.979
Sometimes I see young feminists
talk about bodily autonomy

00:55:35.979 --> 00:55:37.770
and freedom with their
sexuality like we're

00:55:37.770 --> 00:55:39.900
the first people who did this.

00:55:39.900 --> 00:55:43.040
And so one of the things
that's so interesting to me--

00:55:43.040 --> 00:55:46.640
I love, I love
interviewing elders--

00:55:46.640 --> 00:55:51.280
is listening to a 75-year-old
black woman talk about, yeah,

00:55:51.280 --> 00:55:54.860
I brought my girlfriend
to Thanksgiving in '72.

00:55:54.860 --> 00:55:58.490
Yeah, we were out here with
boobs out and butt out,

00:55:58.490 --> 00:56:00.950
and I had my hot pants in '67.

00:56:00.950 --> 00:56:02.450
You know what I'm saying?

00:56:02.450 --> 00:56:04.770
We are not the first
people to do this.

00:56:04.770 --> 00:56:08.900
And that's why a big part of
my feminism, while I think

00:56:08.900 --> 00:56:14.540
that contemporary feminism
is altering our conversation

00:56:14.540 --> 00:56:18.530
in a very unique way, it's
also building on the shoulders

00:56:18.530 --> 00:56:19.760
of those who came before.

00:56:19.760 --> 00:56:23.070
And so I always want
to underscore that.

00:56:23.070 --> 00:56:25.130
And finally, I
love what Dana was

00:56:25.130 --> 00:56:29.840
talking about in her approach
to addressing sexual violence.

00:56:29.840 --> 00:56:34.550
A big part of what I try to
do as a black feminist who

00:56:34.550 --> 00:56:36.790
will hopefully write
a book of theory--

00:56:36.790 --> 00:56:38.540
I am obsessed with theory.

00:56:38.540 --> 00:56:41.780
Bell Hooks says in theory
is liberatory practice.

00:56:41.780 --> 00:56:44.680
Theory has helped me
understand I'm not crazy.

00:56:44.680 --> 00:56:46.430
And I want to help
other people understand

00:56:46.430 --> 00:56:48.560
that they're not crazy.

00:56:48.560 --> 00:56:50.930
But hopefully, what I'm going
to be doing in this work

00:56:50.930 --> 00:56:53.810
is letting people know
that different is possible,

00:56:53.810 --> 00:56:56.210
that we don't have to settle
for what we've been given,

00:56:56.210 --> 00:56:58.790
that it looks hard
and sometimes it's

00:56:58.790 --> 00:57:01.310
not easy for us to imagine.

00:57:01.310 --> 00:57:03.490
What is a world without prisons?

00:57:03.490 --> 00:57:05.510
Well, what does that look like?

00:57:05.510 --> 00:57:08.420
But we can still
make steps forward.

00:57:08.420 --> 00:57:10.670
A new world is possible.

00:57:10.670 --> 00:57:14.185
So that's really what
I'm I'm trying to do.

