01:00:46.010 --> 01:00:51.200
So how does that inform when you
look at the ideas of privilege,

01:00:51.200 --> 01:00:53.640
especially when people
talk about male privilege

01:00:53.640 --> 01:00:55.730
and other privileges,
too, people

01:00:55.730 --> 01:00:57.730
think in terms of people
have it or not have it,

01:00:57.730 --> 01:01:01.600
just static and
totalizing things.

01:01:01.600 --> 01:01:04.700
But that's not reality
in actual practice.

01:01:04.700 --> 01:01:07.810
And I think that's true
for any other people, too.

01:01:07.810 --> 01:01:10.210
But when you talk about
trans women's involvement

01:01:10.210 --> 01:01:13.200
in feminism, that
makes even more clear

01:01:13.200 --> 01:01:19.090
that this idea of totalizing
and static privilege

01:01:19.090 --> 01:01:20.569
is not a real thing.

01:01:20.569 --> 01:01:23.110
And I think that that's kind
of, in fact, one of the examples

01:01:23.110 --> 01:01:27.250
that I think that trans
feminism brings to the feminism.

01:01:27.250 --> 01:01:29.040
So I was writing about that.

01:01:29.040 --> 01:01:31.360
And again, as I said, it's 1999.

01:01:31.360 --> 01:01:36.370
It was limited because
of the historical--

01:01:36.370 --> 01:01:38.800
the terms that I
used at the time

01:01:38.800 --> 01:01:43.870
are not legible today
to people who are not

01:01:43.870 --> 01:01:46.160
aware about the history.

01:01:46.160 --> 01:01:50.300
And it's a historical text, even
though it's only 20 years old.

01:01:50.300 --> 01:01:51.940
It's a historical
text that requires

01:01:51.940 --> 01:01:54.190
the [? historisizing ?]
to understand

01:01:54.190 --> 01:01:56.320
what those things mean.

01:01:56.320 --> 01:01:58.630
When they talk about
how there is virtually

01:01:58.630 --> 01:02:02.860
no representation of trans
men, which is not true now.

01:02:02.860 --> 01:02:05.696
But the time, it
was very much true.

01:02:05.696 --> 01:02:07.570
We had a couple of
friends who are trans men.

01:02:07.570 --> 01:02:10.150
But there wasn't
any organization

01:02:10.150 --> 01:02:13.000
that was headed by trans men
at the time, for example.

01:02:13.000 --> 01:02:15.130
So that was actually
true at the time.

01:02:15.130 --> 01:02:17.720
And it's a totally
different time now.

01:02:17.720 --> 01:02:20.327
So there are weaknesses
because it's historical.

01:02:20.327 --> 01:02:21.910
And also there was
weakness, because I

01:02:21.910 --> 01:02:25.380
was writing in a near void.

01:02:25.380 --> 01:02:27.270
And there was very
little published.

01:02:27.270 --> 01:02:28.770
And especially there
was very little

01:02:28.770 --> 01:02:31.530
published about transfeminism.

01:02:31.530 --> 01:02:33.570
And there was very
little published

01:02:33.570 --> 01:02:35.920
about trans women of color.

01:02:35.920 --> 01:02:38.610
I didn't know
about Sylvia Rivera

01:02:38.610 --> 01:02:41.790
or [INAUDIBLE] at the
time I was writing this

01:02:41.790 --> 01:02:43.740
